about Pam and Larry.

06:12.289 --> 06:18.419
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:18.461 --> 06:20.961
I wanna kiss you so bad
right now,

06:21.006 --> 06:24.256
but they’re watching me.

06:24.301 --> 06:25.471
- I get it.

06:25.510 --> 06:32.480
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:32.517 --> 06:35.137
- I love you, Jake.

06:35.186 --> 06:37.266
- I love you more, Devon.

06:37.314 --> 06:39.274
- That’s not possible.

06:39.316 --> 06:46.406
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:08.845 --> 07:11.095
<i>- ♪ This ain’t no lullaby ♪</i>

07:11.139 --> 07:14.429
<i>♪ But I can make it rhyme
</i> <i>for you, yeah ♪</i>

07:14.476 --> 07:16.306
<i>♪ I can try, I can try ♪</i>

07:16.353 --> 07:18.483
- Jake!

07:18.521 --> 07:20.691
- Wait, wait. Stop, stop, stop!

07:20.732 --> 07:22.022
<i>- ♪ This ain’t on symphony ♪</i>

07:22.067 --> 07:25.027
<i>♪ But if you wanna sing
</i> <i>with me ♪</i>

07:25.070 --> 07:26.700
<i>♪ Then I can try ♪</i>

07:26.738 --> 07:31.238
<i>♪ I can try to lie ♪</i>

07:31.284 --> 07:33.874
<i>♪ In the lullaby ♪</i>

07:33.912 --> 07:38.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:38.750 --> 07:41.710
- Holy secret identity.

07:41.753 --> 07:43.593
- They’re watching.

07:43.630 --> 07:45.340
- I don’t care.

07:45.382 --> 07:48.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:48.802 --> 07:50.142
[laughs]

07:50.178 --> 07:51.758
Um, all right.

07:51.805 --> 07:55.065
Um, I--I’ll see you
this weekend, okay?

07:55.100 --> 07:57.060
All right, cool.

07:57.102 --> 07:58.192
[chuckles]

07:58.228 --> 08:01.858
<i>- ♪ Ooh,
why do you wanna lie? ♪</i>

08:01.898 --> 08:04.728
<i>♪ Why do you wanna lie? ♪</i>

08:04.776 --> 08:07.066
<i>♪ Another lullaby ♪</i>

08:07.112 --> 08:08.992
<i>[dramatic sting]</i>

08:12.409 --> 08:15.369
<i>[spooky music]</i>

08:15.412 --> 08:18.962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:18.999 --> 08:21.079
- Trick or treat!

08:21.126 --> 08:23.246
<i>[man screaming]</i>

08:23.294 --> 08:24.714
[children laughing]

08:24.754 --> 08:27.634
<i>[spooky electronic music]</i>

08:27.674 --> 08:34.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:07.338 --> 09:14.468
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:23.354 --> 09:25.574
[doorbell dings]

09:31.071 --> 09:31.991
- Trick or treat!

09:32.030 --> 09:33.160
- Shit!

09:33.198 --> 09:36.658
[panting]

09:36.701 --> 09:39.001
[doorbell dings]

09:44.709 --> 09:46.209
- You scared me.

09:46.252 --> 09:47.802
- It’s called coulrophobia,

09:47.837 --> 09:49.457
the fear of clowns.

09:49.506 --> 09:52.006
It’s caused
by childhood trauma.

09:52.050 --> 09:53.880
- I’m not afraid
of clowns, all right?

09:53.927 --> 09:55.927
I thought
you were somebody else.

09:55.970 --> 09:58.180
But how old are you?
- Guess.

09:58.223 --> 09:59.683
- What are you doing
out here all alone?

09:59.724 --> 10:01.354
Like, where are your parents?
Your friends?

10:01.392 --> 10:02.892
- They’re dead.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.606
[chatter]
- Trick or treat!

10:05.647 --> 10:07.357
- Okay.

10:07.398 --> 10:12.028
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:12.070 --> 10:13.200
- Boo!

10:13.238 --> 10:15.238
- Jesus.
- [giggles]

10:20.537 --> 10:23.367
<i>- ♪ Five little ghosts
went out one night ♪</i>

10:23.414 --> 10:24.714
[typing]
Shit.

10:24.749 --> 10:26.789
- Holy Halloween costumes,
Batman.

10:26.835 --> 10:28.755
I can’t believe you made these.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.845
- Hey, never forget,
real superheroes can sew.

10:30.880 --> 10:32.880
Is that a little loose?

10:32.924 --> 10:35.514
- Yeah.
- Here, I got it.

10:35.552 --> 10:37.762
The most important thing
in a utility belt

10:37.804 --> 10:40.224
is a bobby pin.
- Good to know.

10:40.265 --> 10:41.725
- Yeah.

10:41.766 --> 10:43.516
All right.

10:43.560 --> 10:46.900
Boy Wonder, the streets are
crawling with bad guys tonight.

10:46.938 --> 10:48.308
It’s time to go fight
some crime.

10:48.356 --> 10:52.066
- And the citizens of Gotham
will pay us in chocolate!

10:52.110 --> 10:54.200
[phone ringing]
- Sorry, Give me a second.

10:54.237 --> 10:57.407
Hello?
<i>- Is Tamara home?</i>

10:57.448 --> 10:59.198
- Who?

10:59.242 --> 11:00.742
<i>- Tamara.</i>

11:00.785 --> 11:03.405
- Uh, think you have
the wrong number.

11:03.454 --> 11:05.674
<i>- Oh, I’m sorry.</i>

11:05.707 --> 11:08.917
- Uh, yeah, it happens.
No worries.

11:08.960 --> 11:09.750
Hm.

11:09.794 --> 11:11.714
[phone ringing]

11:13.423 --> 11:15.843
- Where are you?

11:15.884 --> 11:18.094
Wait, you’re still in Salem?
Jake, what the fuck?

11:18.136 --> 11:19.676
- Holy profanity!

11:19.721 --> 11:23.221
- Oh. Hey, Devon.
I’m here with Gary.

11:23.266 --> 11:24.926
- Excuse my French, Gary.

11:24.976 --> 11:27.226
- Jake’s taking me
trick-or-treating.

11:27.270 --> 11:28.770
- I can see that.

11:28.813 --> 11:30.733
Hey, can I talk to you
for a second?

11:30.773 --> 11:32.733
- Yeah. Um, can you give me
a second, buddy?

11:34.986 --> 11:36.986
- Jake, you know I love
how you look in tights,

11:37.030 --> 11:38.820
but where the hell are you?

11:38.865 --> 11:39.995
- I’m so sorry, Devon.

11:40.033 --> 11:40.993
I’m not gonna be able
to make it.

11:41.034 --> 11:42.794
- You’re telling me this now?

11:42.827 --> 11:43.987
You’re supposed to be
on the bus.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.827
Jake, I’m cooking
for you here, man!

11:45.872 --> 11:47.212
- Pam and Larry
wouldn’t let me go.

11:47.248 --> 11:49.248
They’re--they’re still
not cool with us.

11:49.292 --> 11:51.592
- Screw ’em.
They’re not your real parents.

11:51.628 --> 11:53.298
- Yeah, but they could be.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.128
<i>- Why would you even want them
</i> <i>if they won’t accept you?</i>

11:55.173 --> 11:56.803
<i>- You know, not everyone
</i> <i>is just gonna</i>

11:56.841 --> 11:58.301
<i>get it automatically.</i>

11:58.343 --> 11:59.263
<i>I mean, you lucked out.</i>

11:59.302 --> 12:01.102
- Yeah, my foster mom’s
awesome.

12:01.137 --> 12:02.597
She showed me off
to all of her rich friends,

12:02.639 --> 12:05.429
and then she went to Paris
and I haven’t seen her since.

12:05.475 --> 12:07.815
- You know, Gary’s a good kid.

12:07.852 --> 12:09.442
He deserves a family, too.

12:09.479 --> 12:10.729
He needs me.

12:10.772 --> 12:12.442
- What about me, Jake?

12:12.482 --> 12:13.612
It’s been, like, six months.

12:13.650 --> 12:14.980
I miss you.

12:15.026 --> 12:17.446
- I know.
I miss you too, babe,

12:17.487 --> 12:18.987
but look, I know it sucks,

12:19.030 --> 12:20.820
but let’s just focus
on Christmas break, all right?

12:20.865 --> 12:22.615
- And what am I supposed
to do until then?

12:22.659 --> 12:25.449
Jake, you’re the only one
I can talk to

12:25.495 --> 12:26.835
about what really happened.

12:28.373 --> 12:31.463
- I know. Me too.

12:31.501 --> 12:32.791
- Hey, you heard from Lexy?

12:32.835 --> 12:34.625
- Nope.

12:34.671 --> 12:36.381
- Me neither. Something’s up.

12:36.422 --> 12:37.842
<i>[phone beeps]</i>

12:41.552 --> 12:43.302
- Let’s go, Batman!

12:43.346 --> 12:44.756
- Yeah, um,
I’ll be right there.

12:44.806 --> 12:46.176
Just a second.

12:46.224 --> 12:49.394
- It’s been
125 seconds already.

12:49.435 --> 12:53.225
[phone rings]
126, 127.

12:53.273 --> 12:56.193
- Hello?
<i>- Is Tamara home?</i>

12:56.234 --> 13:00.784
- Uh, still the wrong number.
<i>- Is this 555-0131?</i>

13:00.822 --> 13:03.992
- Yeah, but there’s
no Tamara here.

13:04.033 --> 13:06.203
<i>- Weird.
</i>- Hmm.

13:06.244 --> 13:08.164
<i>- Doing anything fun tonight?</i>

13:08.204 --> 13:09.664
- Uh, yeah, super fun.

13:09.706 --> 13:11.326
I should probably
get back to it.

13:11.374 --> 13:13.424
<i>- How come you’re home
</i> <i>all alone</i>

13:13.459 --> 13:15.209
<i>with your baby brother?</i>

13:15.253 --> 13:18.593
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:18.631 --> 13:19.921
- Who is this?

13:19.966 --> 13:22.376
<i>- Where’s your boyfriend
</i> <i>tonight, Jake?</i>

13:22.427 --> 13:24.217
- Screw you, Ellis.

13:24.262 --> 13:26.222
Douchebag.

13:26.264 --> 13:28.224
[phone rings]

13:28.266 --> 13:29.976
Hey, you know what, Ellis?
You know, it’s bad enough

13:30.018 --> 13:31.558
that you’re
a homophobic douchebag prick.

13:31.602 --> 13:34.062
You know, the really sad thing
is, it’s totally unoriginal!

13:34.105 --> 13:38.235
<i>- This isn’t Ellis.
And I’m not homophobic.</i>

13:38.276 --> 13:42.196
<i>I don’t discriminate based
on anyone’s sexual preference.</i>

13:42.238 --> 13:44.698
<i>That’s not why I’m calling.</i>

13:44.741 --> 13:46.081
- Then why the hell
are you calling?

13:46.117 --> 13:48.327
<i>- To make sure you’re home.</i>

13:48.369 --> 13:49.949
<i>Happy Halloween.</i>

13:49.996 --> 13:52.916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:52.957 --> 13:54.707
[doorbell dings]
- I’ll get it!

13:54.751 --> 13:56.711
- No, no, no! I’ll get it.

13:56.753 --> 13:59.713
<i>[intense music]</i>

13:59.756 --> 14:05.546
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:15.355 --> 14:16.985
[sighs]

14:20.985 --> 14:23.565
[phone rings]

14:23.613 --> 14:25.113
Hey.

14:25.156 --> 14:27.196
- Jake, I just got a weird call
from this douchebag.

14:27.241 --> 14:28.581
- Wait, he called you too?

14:28.618 --> 14:31.288
I think it’s Ellis, that
Neanderthal from my school.

14:33.206 --> 14:36.076
But I don’t know, he--

14:36.125 --> 14:38.915
didn’t he sound kinda...
familiar?

14:38.961 --> 14:42.091
