Just send someone now!

16:12.138 --> 16:13.678
- Come on, Lexy, pick up!

16:14.223 --> 16:17.103
- [laughs]
[phone buzzing]

16:17.143 --> 16:19.563
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:19.604 --> 16:22.024
<i>[line trilling]</i>

16:23.566 --> 16:26.146
- You gonna get that?
- Nope.

16:29.780 --> 16:31.120
- No!

16:31.157 --> 16:38.287
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.289 --> 16:49.509
<i>- ♪ All I do is
tease my heart ♪</i>

16:49.550 --> 16:51.720
<i>♪ ’Cause time after time
</i> <i>it yearns ♪</i>

16:51.761 --> 16:54.561
<i>♪ But I’m dedicated, and in
</i> <i>the hustle and bustle ♪</i>

16:54.597 --> 16:55.927
- You sure about this?

16:55.973 --> 16:58.023
- Absolutely.

16:58.059 --> 16:59.979
- But your mother.

17:00.019 --> 17:03.609
- She won’t be home for hours,
if at all.

17:03.648 --> 17:05.728
- Your sister?

17:05.775 --> 17:06.985
- Trust me,
I have her well-trained.

17:07.026 --> 17:08.436
She’s not gonna bother us.

17:09.737 --> 17:12.737
<i>- ♪ I crawl back to you
</i> <i>in the deep ♪</i>

17:12.782 --> 17:15.122
<i>♪ Wanna walk on water,
but I can’t find my feet ♪</i>

17:15.159 --> 17:16.409
<i>♪ Yeah, so I crawl back
</i> <i>to you ♪</i>

17:16.452 --> 17:19.962
- Um--Lexy, you have
done this before, right?

17:21.582 --> 17:22.922
- Have you?

17:24.585 --> 17:26.705
- I think your first time
should be special.

17:26.754 --> 17:30.094
<i>- ♪ So I crawl back,
I crawl back to you ♪</i>

17:30.132 --> 17:33.222
- Okay, first,
I just need a bump.

17:33.261 --> 17:34.511
- Me too.

17:38.808 --> 17:41.728
<i>[tense music]</i>

17:41.769 --> 17:45.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:45.648 --> 17:47.778
- [sniffs]

17:47.817 --> 17:50.107
[coughs]

17:50.152 --> 17:53.322
- Lexy, I really like you.

17:53.364 --> 17:54.824
- Thanks.

17:57.952 --> 17:58.992
- [sniffs]

17:59.036 --> 18:05.456
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:05.501 --> 18:06.791
This just feels right,
doesn’t it?

18:06.836 --> 18:07.956
- Please stop talking.

18:09.839 --> 18:12.969
- No! No, don’t!

18:13.009 --> 18:15.389
- Police!
- Jesus Christ!

18:15.428 --> 18:16.468
- You kids okay?

18:16.512 --> 18:17.762
- What the hell
are you doing here?

18:17.805 --> 18:18.805
Did my mother send you?

18:18.848 --> 18:20.348
- We got a report
of a break-in.

18:20.391 --> 18:22.021
I’m gonna have a look around.
- Yeah.

18:22.059 --> 18:24.139
- I should go.
- Sit down.

18:26.022 --> 18:28.822
- Did the alarm go off?
- No. Someone called us.

18:28.858 --> 18:30.728
Do you know a Devon Evans?

18:30.776 --> 18:33.696
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:33.738 --> 18:35.028
- Yeah, I do.

18:35.072 --> 18:39.662
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:39.702 --> 18:41.332
[screams]
Help!

18:43.122 --> 18:45.372
- Was there anyone else
in the house tonight?

18:45.416 --> 18:48.416
- The ghost of Halloween past.

18:48.461 --> 18:50.001
- Who?

18:50.046 --> 18:53.836
- He asked to use the bathroom.
He said it was an emergency.

18:53.883 --> 18:56.223
Then he said see ya later.

18:56.260 --> 18:59.970
- Caroline, how tall
was this ghost?

19:00.014 --> 19:02.314
- Well, he was about this tall.

19:04.894 --> 19:06.064
- There’s nobody here.

19:06.103 --> 19:07.563
No sign of forced entry,
either.

19:07.605 --> 19:09.365
- Any dolls?

19:09.398 --> 19:11.528
- What?

19:11.567 --> 19:15.237
- Oh, no.
Lexy, I think it was--

19:15.279 --> 19:17.869
- Officer, this is just
a misunderstanding.

19:17.907 --> 19:20.077
My sister shouldn’t be inviting
strangers into the house,

19:20.117 --> 19:21.907
no matter how bad
they have to pee!

19:23.871 --> 19:26.871
Would you mind staying with us
until my mother gets home?

19:26.916 --> 19:28.876
She’ll be pissed off
if you don’t.

19:28.918 --> 19:32.088
- Sure.

19:32.129 --> 19:34.049
- You can go.
- Thanks.

19:38.386 --> 19:40.886
- He said he liked
to be hugged.

19:40.930 --> 19:44.220
He said he was my friend
till the end.

19:44.266 --> 19:48.396
At first,
he seemed really nice,

19:48.437 --> 19:50.897
but he lied.

19:50.940 --> 19:53.400
He had secrets.

19:53.442 --> 19:56.612
Chucky always had secrets.

19:56.654 --> 20:00.284
- Caroline, what were
Chucky’s secrets?

20:01.200 --> 20:02.910
- He killed a lot of people...

20:02.952 --> 20:04.832
- [screaming]

20:04.870 --> 20:08.620
[crowd screaming]

20:08.666 --> 20:09.956
- Including my daddy.

20:10.876 --> 20:13.296
[people screaming]

20:13.337 --> 20:16.467
- Caroline, you know
that it was Junior Wheeler

20:16.507 --> 20:17.927
who did that.

20:17.967 --> 20:21.007
- Your sister’s boyfriend.

20:21.053 --> 20:22.603
Right, Lexy?

20:22.638 --> 20:25.928
- No. Tell them, Lexy.

20:25.975 --> 20:28.195
You saw him, too.

20:28.227 --> 20:30.517
And now he’s back.

20:30.563 --> 20:33.943
Chucky was the ghost
of Halloween past.

20:33.983 --> 20:36.533
Tell them, Lexy.
It was Chucky.

20:38.487 --> 20:40.447
- No.

20:40.489 --> 20:43.449
No, Caroline, it was Junior.

20:43.492 --> 20:45.952
Junior killed all those people.

20:45.995 --> 20:47.705
Chucky is only a doll.

20:50.708 --> 20:52.668
I mean, was.

20:52.710 --> 20:55.340
- You understand that,
don’t you, Caroline?

20:55.379 --> 20:57.339
- You can’t blame her
for having a hard time

20:57.381 --> 21:00.341
accepting that her own sister

21:00.384 --> 21:03.684
could invite a boy like that
into our lives.

21:03.721 --> 21:06.061
- You never liked him,

21:06.098 --> 21:07.978
not even before
he killed anyone.

21:08.017 --> 21:09.687
- Exactly.

21:09.727 --> 21:11.727
I’ve always been able
to read people,

21:11.771 --> 21:14.981
and I could tell from day one
he was bad news.

21:15.024 --> 21:16.904
- No.

21:16.942 --> 21:18.822
He wasn’t always like that.

21:20.863 --> 21:22.533
He was the sweetest boy
in the world.

21:22.573 --> 21:25.203
- That boy
destroyed everything.

21:25.242 --> 21:27.702
Your father,

21:27.745 --> 21:29.415
very possibly my career,

21:29.455 --> 21:32.005
if you haven’t seen
the latest polls,

21:32.041 --> 21:33.711
and your sister’s childhood.

21:35.044 --> 21:36.634
She can’t even sleep
without waking up

21:36.670 --> 21:39.260
screaming every night
from the nightmares.

21:40.674 --> 21:43.554
And she made me
get rid of all of her dolls.

21:43.594 --> 21:46.144
- Yes, it’s called pediophobia.

21:46.180 --> 21:48.720
That’s the clinical term
for fear of dolls.

21:49.600 --> 21:51.600
- Sadly, it’s the least
of our problems.

21:51.644 --> 21:55.404
- Actually, I think it might be

21:55.439 --> 21:57.439
the ideal place to start.

21:58.400 --> 21:59.860
- What do you mean?

21:59.902 --> 22:03.532
- I’d like to try something,
if you’ll permit me.

22:03.572 --> 22:05.532
- Um, okay.

22:05.574 --> 22:09.294
- You know, I collect dolls,
recreationally.

22:10.037 --> 22:12.957
Since I was Caroline’s age.

22:12.998 --> 22:14.578
As a child, I had polio.

22:14.625 --> 22:18.925
I was stuck in bed
for two years.

22:18.963 --> 22:20.673
My babies were my only friends.

22:23.425 --> 22:26.715
It really is
a fascinating hobby.

22:26.762 --> 22:33.602
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:33.644 --> 22:35.274
This is Belle.

22:38.190 --> 22:41.780
Wedding Belle, they called her.

22:41.819 --> 22:44.279
She is incredibly rare,

22:44.321 --> 22:46.281
a marketing concept
from the ’90s.

22:46.323 --> 22:48.623
They made very few of these.

22:48.659 --> 22:51.909
I use her sometimes
for therapeutic purposes.

22:52.746 --> 22:55.116
Caroline, I think
Belle could help you.

22:56.000 --> 22:57.710
Would you like to hold her?

22:59.420 --> 23:02.420
- Go ahead, sweetheart.
You can do it.

23:05.676 --> 23:09.176
- There. Oh.
[chuckles]

23:09.221 --> 23:11.811
I think she likes you.

23:11.849 --> 23:13.889
She needs someone
to take care of her.

23:15.519 --> 23:16.769
Would you like
to take her home?

23:19.023 --> 23:20.483
- Sure.

23:22.776 --> 23:24.606
- She’ll be a good friend
to you.

23:25.779 --> 23:27.859
- Oh, I’m so proud of you,
sweetheart.

23:27.907 --> 23:29.867
<i>So, so proud.</i>

23:29.909 --> 23:31.909
<i>[sinister music]</i>

23:31.952 --> 23:34.002
[camera shutter clicks]

23:34.038 --> 23:35.328
- Mrs. Cross,

23:35.372 --> 23:36.922
thank you for inviting me
into your lovely home.

23:36.957 --> 23:40.497
- Oh, thank you, James.
And please, call me Michelle.

23:40.544 --> 23:44.344
- Michelle, do you miss living
in the mayor’s residence?

23:44.381 --> 23:48.141
- Oh, you know,
that’s a beautiful house.

23:48.177 --> 23:50.097
But my late husband used to say

23:50.137 --> 23:51.927
we were really
just its caretakers

23:51.972 --> 23:54.022
for a brief period of time,

23:54.058 --> 23:57.348
a blip in Hackensack’s history.

23:57.394 --> 24:00.864
- But after voters
overwhelmingly recalled you

24:00.898 --> 24:03.688
from office
after the murders last year,

24:03.734 --> 24:07.454
the single most violent era
in our city’s history,

24:07.488 --> 24:09.028
you’re running
for a second term.

24:09.073 --> 24:13.163
And I have to ask,
why do you deserve my vote now?

24:13.202 --> 24:15.872
- As a survivor
of violence myself,

24:15.913 --> 24:20.883
I think I occupy
a unique position of empathy

24:20.918 --> 24:23.798
for everyone who lost somebody
in last year’s tragic events.

24:23.837 --> 24:26.047
I know exactly
what they’re going through

24:26.090 --> 24:30.050
because I’m going
through it, too.

24:30.094 --> 24:32.894
The grief, the anger,

24:32.930 --> 24:36.680
the guilt...
the survivor’s guilt.

24:38.018 --> 24:41.398
But I promise
every citizen of Hackensack

24:41.438 --> 24:43.398
that in my second term
as mayor,

24:43.440 --> 24:46.190
I will show no mercy
to violent offenders.

24:46.235 --> 24:49.205
One strike and you’re out.
[chuckles]

24:49.238 --> 24:51.568
- I heard you had a break-in
here just last night.

24:51.615 --> 24:52.945
What would you say to the perp?

24:52.992 --> 24:55.082
- I’d just like to dare them
to try that again

24:55.119 --> 24:57.749
while I’m home.

24:57.788 --> 25:00.498
- And how about you, Lexy?
How are you holding up?

25:02.001 --> 25:06.511
- Um, well, it’s been
a really tough year.

25:06.547 --> 25:09.967
But I’m getting through it
with my family’s help.

25:10.009 --> 25:11.929
- We’re getting
through it together.

25:11.969 --> 25:14.759
Like all of us in Hackensack,
we’re strong.

25:15.973 --> 25:17.933
Hackensack strong!

25:17.975 --> 25:21.315
- Caroline, how about you?
- I’m fine.

25:21.353 --> 25:24.443
- Hey, whatever happened
to Chucky?

25:24.481 --> 25:26.441
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:26.483 --> 25:29.613
- Um, excuse me?

25:29.653 --> 25:32.283
- As I recall, she used
to drag that thing everywhere.

25:33.532 --> 25:36.122
- Um, well, she has
a new doll now.

25:36.160 --> 25:37.830
Her name is Belle.

25:37.870 --> 25:41.750
- Caroline, does Belle
tell you to do things, too?

25:41.790 --> 25:43.920
- What are you talking about?

25:43.959 --> 25:47.379
- Well, at a press conference
last year, she said--

25:47.421 --> 25:49.261
- Chucky told me to kill Mommy.

25:49.298 --> 25:51.378
- Uh--
- Who is Chucky?

25:51.425 --> 25:54.265
- Um, thank you so much.
- I’m sorry. Kids.

25:54.303 --> 25:55.473
- Remember?

25:55.512 --> 25:57.182
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:57.222 --> 25:58.972
- Get out of my house.

25:59.016 --> 26:00.676
- We have it on tape.

26:00.726 --> 26:02.436
- Get out!

26:02.478 --> 26:09.568
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:13.864 --> 26:16.284
- Dr. Mixter is full of shit.

26:16.325 --> 26:18.955
- [sighs]
I knew it.

26:18.994 --> 26:20.294
- Mom, too.

26:20.329 --> 26:23.289
<i>[tense music]</i>

26:23.332 --> 26:29.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:30.881 --> 26:33.801
[grunting]

26:43.352 --> 26:46.442
[breathing heavily]

26:52.903 --> 26:55.283
You should be afraid, Caroline.

26:55.322 --> 26:57.032
Dolls are horrifying.

26:57.074 --> 26:59.584
Never trust any doll.
They’re all fucked up.

27:00.744 --> 27:03.044
- You said the F-word.

27:03.080 --> 27:06.040
- Yes. I know what I said.

27:08.877 --> 27:10.917
That is how serious
this is, Caroline.

27:12.756 --> 27:15.586
Now say it.
Dolls are fucked up.

27:17.261 --> 27:19.681
- Dolls are fucked up.

27:19.721 --> 27:21.891
- Never trust any doll.

27:21.932 --> 27:25.232
- Never trust any doll.
- Okay, good.

27:25.269 --> 27:26.559
And you can’t tell anyone,

27:26.603 --> 27:28.983
or they’re gonna send you away,
okay?

27:29.022 --> 27:30.362
- Okay.

27:30.399 --> 27:32.069
- Cross your heart.

27:32.109 --> 27:33.689
- Cross my heart.

27:35.404 --> 27:36.954
- Okay, and...

27:36.989 --> 27:41.529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:41.577 --> 27:42.907
Keep this handy.

27:46.957 --> 27:48.327
Sweet dreams.

27:48.375 --> 27:55.465
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:24.077 --> 28:25.537
- Jake!

28:32.002 --> 28:33.132
- Oh--

28:37.090 --> 28:39.300
- You Ubered here
all the way from Salem?

28:39.343 --> 28:41.433
I can’t just sneak off
in the middle of the night.

28:41.470 --> 28:44.220
Neither can you. Do Pam and--
- We have to get Lexy, okay?

28:45.849 --> 28:47.309
Have you seen this?

28:47.351 --> 28:49.141
- Yeah, it looks familiar.

28:49.186 --> 28:51.146
- If Chucky really was
at her house last night,

28:51.188 --> 28:53.648
then why didn’t he kill her
when he had the chance?

28:53.690 --> 28:56.150
- Maybe he’s just messing
with us.

28:56.193 --> 28:59.153
Or maybe he’s trying
to get one of us to kill again.

28:59.196 --> 29:01.106
- [exhales]

29:01.156 --> 29:02.696
Let’s go.
- Yeah.

29:02.741 --> 29:05.621
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:05.661 --> 29:10.958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:10.958 --> 29:21.178
<i>- ♪ Uh, uh, baby,
you’re the devil I know ♪</i>

29:21.218 --> 29:24.008
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

29:24.054 --> 29:26.264
<i>♪ Better than the devil
</i> <i>I don’t ♪</i>

29:26.306 --> 29:29.096
<i>♪ I don’t ♪</i>

29:29.142 --> 29:30.442
[knock at window]
<i>♪ Maybe I could stop ♪</i>

29:30.477 --> 29:34.607
<i>♪ But I won’t, I won’t ♪</i>

29:34.648 --> 29:37.148
<i>♪ ’Cause, baby,
you’re the devil I know ♪</i>

29:37.192 --> 29:40.532
<i>♪ I know, I know ♪</i>

29:40.570 --> 29:42.530
- Hey.
- Hi.

29:42.572 --> 29:44.872
- Careful. Hey.

29:44.908 --> 29:47.198
Shh, my mom’s downstairs.
- Sorry.

29:47.244 --> 29:48.334
- It took you long enough.

29:48.370 --> 29:49.870
- Yeah, it’s nice
to see you, too.

29:49.913 --> 29:51.663
- Hey.

29:53.292 --> 29:54.332
- This place isn’t bad.

29:54.376 --> 29:55.586
I thought you said
it was a dump.

29:55.627 --> 29:57.457
- Please.
I can’t even talk about it.

29:57.504 --> 29:58.964
It’s like I’ve been demoted.

29:59.006 --> 30:02.046
- I thought you quit.
- I’m sorry, Jake.

30:02.092 --> 30:05.302
When did you stop medicating
your chronic anxiety?

30:05.345 --> 30:07.885
- It’s not the same thing.

30:07.931 --> 30:10.061
- It’s just a little weed.
What’s the big deal?

30:10.100 --> 30:12.190
- Oh, no big deal,

30:12.227 --> 30:15.057
if that’s all you’re doing.

30:15.105 --> 30:16.235
Is it?

30:16.273 --> 30:18.733
- Yes, that’s all I’m doing.

30:18.775 --> 30:20.565
Jesus, I haven’t seen you
in six months.

30:20.610 --> 30:23.030
You’re acting like
this is an intervention.

30:23.071 --> 30:24.611
We have serious shit
to deal with.

30:26.116 --> 30:28.236
Devon, what did you find out
about Caroline’s doll?

30:28.285 --> 30:31.335
- Well, she looks a little
like the Bride of Chucky.

30:31.371 --> 30:32.751
Remember that movie?

30:32.789 --> 30:35.789
- Yeah, with Jennifer Tilly,

30:35.834 --> 30:38.634
who we know really is
the Bride of Chucky,

30:38.670 --> 30:40.880
Tiffany Valentine.

30:40.922 --> 30:42.382
- Shit.

30:42.424 --> 30:44.264
- Where’s that doll now?

30:44.301 --> 30:47.261
<i>[ominous music]</i>

30:47.304 --> 30:48.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:48.972 --> 30:51.272
[door creaks]

30:51.308 --> 30:58.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:05.655 --> 31:07.655
- Maybe it’s just
a coincidence.

31:07.699 --> 31:09.659
- Did you test it?

31:09.701 --> 31:12.621
- Yeah, I bashed the shit
out of it.

31:12.662 --> 31:14.962
And it came from our therapist.

31:14.998 --> 31:17.128
I mean, our family therapist
can’t be in league

31:17.167 --> 31:19.837
with a supernaturally
possessed doll, right?

31:19.878 --> 31:21.628
- Lexy?

31:21.671 --> 31:24.591
- Shit, it’s my mom.
Um, get in the closet!

31:37.687 --> 31:38.857
- What’s going on?

31:38.897 --> 31:41.067
- I was just checking
on Caroline.

31:42.692 --> 31:44.072
- Well, who were you
talking to?

31:45.779 --> 31:48.819
- I was singing her a lullaby,

31:48.865 --> 31:50.155
the way Dad used to.

31:50.200 --> 31:52.040
- Oh.

31:52.077 --> 31:53.907
Look at her. Aww.

31:55.831 --> 31:57.961
I don’t think she’s slept
like that in months.

31:59.793 --> 32:02.003
Maybe our luck
has finally turned around.

32:03.880 --> 32:06.050
- Maybe.

32:06.091 --> 32:07.841
- Okay.

32:07.884 --> 32:09.684
We should leave her be.
Come on.

32:12.597 --> 32:13.967
[door click shut]

32:14.641 --> 32:21.771
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:23.233 --> 32:25.993
[door creaks]

32:31.074 --> 32:32.704
[door shuts]

32:32.742 --> 32:39.832
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:46.506 --> 32:49.466
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

32:49.509 --> 32:56.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:04.065 --> 33:06.525
- Caroline, what did
I tell you last night?

33:06.568 --> 33:08.068
- Belle’s okay.

33:08.111 --> 33:11.741
She’s not like Chucky.
She’s just a doll.

33:11.781 --> 33:15.741
And I don’t want Mommy
to get mad anymore.

33:15.785 --> 33:18.115
- Where is she?
- She left already.

33:18.163 --> 33:21.003
She said you have
to walk me to school.

33:21.041 --> 33:23.001
- Okay. I’ll be right back.

33:31.301 --> 33:32.591
Here.

33:35.472 --> 33:36.722
Look, guys, I’ve been thinking,

33:36.765 --> 33:40.065
and maybe the other night
really just was a prank.

33:41.144 --> 33:43.904
I mean, we were pretty famous
for a while after the murders,

33:43.939 --> 33:45.769
and there are
some sick assholes out there

33:45.815 --> 33:47.275
with way too much time
on their hands.

33:47.317 --> 33:48.777
- Yeah, some sick asshole

33:48.818 --> 33:50.068
